title: Web visualization basic pages
body:
The first iteration for the new debugging charts.

This PR creates a replacement for the training viewer panel. Future PRs will add the action inversion check tools.

The primary focus on this PR is functionality. It's very possible we can make the code to assemble the data more efficient. We can do this as needed. I do have one large object_logging dir I created for testing this and may do some benchmarking as follow-on work. The UX is much more response than the matplotlib-based one.

Recommendation to reviewer: 
I propose skimming or skipping the css, html, and js files. Review the python and also try it out (all feedback or making changes yourself very welcome!). 

Run command:
rome-wasnt-built-in-a-day/tools/web$ `python sibyl.py --log_dir ../../object_logging`

Then visit:
http://127.0.0.1:5000/training_history

title: Training history filters
body:
Amend the object log reader API to include filters for start and end batch index.

This feature is primarily to support pruning data for debugging query use-cases.

title: Object log cache for efficient access.
body:
Creates a simple cache to load and store object log files for single-threaded access from the debug visualization web server.

Loading the files imposes a non-trivial delay.
